# Development Workflow

## Running the Project

Always prefer `task` commands over raw docker/bun commands in docs and scripts.

| Mode | Command | When to use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| Local (hybrid) | `task local` | Daily development — fast hot reload |
| Cloudflare local | `task cf:dev` | Test Workers + D1 via wrangler |
| Cloudflare deploy | `task deploy:cloudflare` | Production deploy (Workers + Pages + D1) |
| Dev (full Docker) | `task dev` | When Bun is not installed on host |
| Prod (legacy Pi) | `task prod` | Deprecated — use Cloudflare |
| DB admin | `task db-admin` | Browse SQLite (dev only) |

### URLs
- Frontend: http://localhost:4000
- Backend API: http://localhost:4001/api/health
- DB Admin (optional): http://localhost:8080
- Production (via Nginx): http://localhost (port 80)

## Taskfile Conventions

- All run/stop/log tasks live in [Taskfile.yml](../../Taskfile.yml) at project root
- Use `vars` for compose file paths — do not duplicate compose commands inline
- New services added to `docker-compose.dev.yml` or `docker-compose.prod.yml` MUST get corresponding tasks (start, stop, logs)
- Interactive tasks (`local`, `dev`, `dev:logs`, `prod:logs`) use `interactive: true`

## Bun Conventions

- Package manager: Bun only (`bun install`, `bun run dev`, `bun run build`)
- Lockfile: `frontend/bun.lock` — never generate or commit `package-lock.json`
- Frontend Dockerfile uses `oven/bun:1-alpine`

## Docker Compose Files

- `docker-compose.dev.yml` — development (backend + optional frontend container + db-admin profile)
- `docker-compose.prod.yml` — production (backend + built frontend + Nginx)
- `docker-compose.yml` — base/shared service definitions

## Documentation

- When updating setup instructions, update [README.md](../../README.md) Task Commands table
- Do not hardcode `docker compose -f ...` in new docs — reference task names instead
